Role: Expert Full-Stack Developer.
Task: Build a SaaS web application for a "Meeting Coordination Platform".
Tech Stack: Next.js (App Router) with TypeScript, React, Tailwind CSS, Lucide-React (icons), and Supabase (for PostgreSQL database and Authentication). Assume deployment to Vercel.

Core Features to Implement:

Database Schema (Supabase): Design relational tables for Users (Directory), Templates, Meetings (instances), and Checklists. Handle recurrence logic by linking instances to a parent series ID.

Template Builder: A UI to create meeting templates with custom attributes (Chairman, Coordinator) and a default checklist of tasks.

Scheduling Engine: Ability to schedule "Ad-hoc" (one-off) or "Recurring" meetings (Daily/Weekly/Monthly).

Outlook-Style Logic: When editing or canceling a recurring meeting, prompt the user: "This occurrence only" or "Entire series."

Dual-View Dashboard: >    - List View: Table showing Meeting Name, Date, Progress (%), and Status. Include a "More Info" icon that shows a rich-text description in a popover.

Calendar View: Monthly grid with color-coded "pills" (Green: On Track, Amber: Holiday Conflict, Grey: Cancelled).

People Directory & Tagging: A manual "User Management" section to add people (Name, Division, Rank). In any checklist task, allow typing "@" to trigger a searchable autocomplete dropdown of these users from the Supabase DB.

Holiday Logic: Cross-reference a mock public holiday list. Display an amber "Warning Badge" if a meeting or task falls on a holiday.

Status Management: Cancelled meetings should remain in the dashboard but appear greyed out and struck-through. Update their status in the database without deleting the row.

Technical Requirements:

Use strict TypeScript: Define clear interfaces and types for all database models (User, Template, Meeting, ChecklistTask) before building the UI.

Create a highly modular folder structure using Next.js App Router conventions (/app, /components, /lib/supabase).

Use Tailwind CSS for a professional, "Enterprise SaaS" aesthetic (clean whites, greys, and primary blue accents).

Ensure all views (List, Calendar, Template Builder, People Management) are accessible via a persistent sidebar navigation.